QUESTITEM_TRANSFER_LETTER.Description: Recommends you for further service at a higher level.

QUESTITEM_LIGHT_BLUEPRINTS.Description: Explains how to construct sensible buildings.

QUESTITEM_LIGHT_MANUSCRIPTS.Description: The topmost manuscript is titled: 'Our Glorious King Who is Bold and Not That Racist' by John Quillmaster.

QUESTITEM_LIGHT_SURVEYS.Description: You leaf through the stack of papers. You realize you don't find rocks particularly interesting. You put the papers down...

QUESTITEM_HEAVY_MORTAR.Description: The kind you build walls with. It's pretty heavy.

QUESTITEM_HEAVY_CRATE.Description: Big wooden boxes, mainly for the shipment of solid goods.

QUESTITEM_HEAVY_BARREL.Description: Big wooden barrels, mainly for the shipment of liquids, grains and the like.

QUESTITEM_LIGHT_FUR.Description: Useful for keeping warm. Stinks to high heaven.

QUESTITEM_LIGHT_PATROLROUTE.Description: Orders for fresh patrol routes around the King's various territories.

QUESTITEM_HEAVY_MOONSHINE.Real Name: Delivery: Geoff the Brigand's All-Natural Enriched Moonshine
QUESTITEM_HEAVY_MOONSHINE.Description: "Guaranteed free of unnatural flavourings, colourings or preservatives", according to the label.

QUESTITEM_LIGHT_KITTENS.Description: Someone has stitched "NOT TOO B THRON IN RIVAR" on the side.

QUESTITEM_LIGHT_OLDCLOTHES.Description: A big pile of old clothes, barely used. Probably fashionable once upon a time.

QUESTITEM_HEAVY_FARMTOOLS.Description: Tools suitable both for shoeing hooves and preparing delicious cheese-based dishes.

QUESTITEM_LIGHT_ASSASSINATION.Description: Order for the assassination of a key enemy figure. Comes with the Royal stamp.

QUESTITEM_LIGHT_CASUALTIES.Description: Lists all the casualties experienced by a unit in the past week. There's quite a lot...

QUESTITEM_LIGHT_RINGS.Description: Rings used to identify military leaders who otherwise could not be identified after battle.

QUESTITEM_HEAVY_MEDICAL.Description: A large quantity of military-issue medical supplies. Somebody is expecting trouble...

QUESTITEM_HEAVY_FIREBARREL.Description: The warnings plastered all over the outside make it abundantly clear that these barrels do not contain anything mundane. The cumulative effect of all the instructions is that they should not be touched, moved or looked at, ever.

QUESTITEM_TOKEN_ARENA_UNRANKED.Description: Discontinued Item. This can no longer be traded in for Arena-specific rewards, but can be salvaged for the chance of obtaining a Royal Sigil.

QUESTITEM_TOKEN_ARENA_CRYSTAL.Description: A Sigil for defeating your opponent in the Arena. You can buy Arena specific-rewards from the Arena Master with these Sigils.

QUESTITEM_TOKEN_AVALON.Description: A flask emanating immense power. Can be used to craft a variety of items.

QUESTITEM_TOKEN_MISTS.Description: A local resource which can be purchased in Brecilien with Favor.

QUESTITEM_TOKEN_ROYAL_HORSE.Description: Once this could buy a noble steed... now all it's worth is what collectors want to pay for it!

QUESTITEM_TOKEN_UNDEAD.Description: Recognizes the bearer's generosity to the fallen.

QUESTITEM_TOKEN_ADC_FRAME.Description: This token is achieved by salvaging an Adventurer's Challenge Avatar Ring. It can be exchanged for special rewards at the Vanity Merchant.

T2_MOUNT_MULE.Description: Simple mount, given to new arrivals to the lands of Albion.

T3_MOUNT_HORSE.Description: Horses are commonly used for travel throughout Albion, and provide the fastest means of getting around.

T4_MOUNT_HORSE.Description: Lean and agile, Albion horses can carry their riders quickly across the continent, but have little strength to bear heavy items.

T5_MOUNT_HORSE.Description: Lean and agile, Albion horses can carry their riders quickly across the continent, but have little strength to bear heavy items.

T8_MOUNT_HORSE.Description: Lean and agile, Albion horses can carry their riders quickly across the continent, but have little strength to bear heavy items.

T5_MOUNT_ARMORED_HORSE.Description: Protected by thick plating, an armored horse is ideal for traveling through Albion's more dangerous regions at speed.

T6_MOUNT_ARMORED_HORSE.Description: Protected by thick plating, an armored horse is ideal for traveling through Albion's more dangerous regions at speed.

T7_MOUNT_ARMORED_HORSE.Description: Protected by thick plating, an armored horse is ideal for traveling through Albion's more dangerous regions at speed.

T8_MOUNT_ARMORED_HORSE.Description: Protected by thick plating, an armored horse is ideal for traveling through Albion's more dangerous regions at speed.

T3_MOUNT_OX.Description: Albion oxen are tough, and sturdy enough to carry large quantities of goods, but cannot match the pace of the continent's horses.

T4_MOUNT_OX.Description: Albion oxen are tough, and sturdy enough to carry large quantities of goods, but cannot match the pace of the continent's horses.

T5_MOUNT_OX.Description: Albion oxen are tough, and sturdy enough to carry large quantities of goods, but cannot match the pace of the continent's horses.

T7_MOUNT_OX.Description: Albion oxen are tough, and sturdy enough to carry large quantities of goods, but cannot match the pace of the continent's horses.

T8_MOUNT_OX.Description: Oxen are commonly used for transporting large quantities of items in Albion, as they are slow but are not easily stopped.

T4_MOUNT_GIANTSTAG.Description: Stags are fast and strong, making them favored mounts of gatherers and couriers.

T6_MOUNT_GIANTSTAG_MOOSE.Description: Moose are fast and strong, making them favored mounts of gatherers and couriers.

T6_MOUNT_DIREWOLF.Description: One of Albion's fastest mounts, the Direwolf specializes in hunting, pursuit, and evasion.

T8_MOUNT_MAMMOTH_TRANSPORT.Description: What a mammoth lacks in speed, it makes up for in enormous carrying capacity. Mammoths are the favored transport of anyone wishing to move really, really large quantities of goods.

T5_MOUNT_MOABIRD_FW_BRIDGEWATCH.Description: Mount - A special breed originally from the steppe around Bridgewatch.

T5_MOUNT_DIREBEAR_FW_FORTSTERLING.Description: Mount - A special breed originally from the mountains around Fort Sterling.

T5_MOUNT_DIREBOAR_FW_LYMHURST.Description: Mount - A special breed originally from the forests around Lymhurst.

T5_MOUNT_RAM_FW_MARTLOCK.Description: Mount - A special breed originally from the highlands around Martlock.

T5_MOUNT_SWAMPDRAGON_FW_THETFORD.Description: Mount - A special breed originally from the swamps around Thetford.

T5_MOUNT_GREYWOLF_FW_CAERLEON.Description: Mount - A special breed originally from the area around Caerleon.

T5_MOUNT_OWL_FW_BRECILIEN.Description: A Mystic Owl that can only be found in the Mists.

T8_MOUNT_MOABIRD_FW_BRIDGEWATCH_ELITE.Description: Mount - A special breed, raised for combat, from the steppe around Bridgewatch.

T8_MOUNT_DIREBEAR_FW_FORTSTERLING_ELITE.Description: Mount - A special breed, raised for combat, from the mountains around Fort Sterling.

T8_MOUNT_DIREBOAR_FW_LYMHURST_ELITE.Description: Mount - A special breed, raised for combat, from the forests around Lymhurst.

T8_MOUNT_RAM_FW_MARTLOCK_ELITE.Description: Mount - A special breed, raised for combat, from the highlands around Martlock.

T8_MOUNT_SWAMPDRAGON_FW_THETFORD_ELITE.Description: Mount - A special breed, raised for combat, from the swamps around Thetford.

T8_MOUNT_GREYWOLF_FW_CAERLEON_ELITE.Description: Mount - A special breed, raised for combat, from the area around Caerleon.

T8_MOUNT_OWL_FW_BRECILIEN_ELITE.Description: A Mystic Owl that has been trained and equipped to traverse the Mists and use their magic.

T8_MOUNT_MAMMOTH_BATTLE@1.Description: Battle Mount - This war mammoth's command platform allows its rider to direct and bolster allies. Immune to crowd control.

T7_MOUNT_SWAMPDRAGON_BATTLE.Description: Battle Mount - This mount can breathe fire on enemies and ignite them from a distance. Immune to displacement effects.

T7_MOUNT_ARMORED_SWAMPDRAGON_BATTLE.Description: Battle Mount - This armored mount can lunge at enemies and poison them. Immune to displacement effects.

T6_MOUNT_SIEGE_BALLISTA.Description: Battle Mount - Immune to displacement effects.

T8_MOUNT_HORSE_UNDEAD@1.Description: Secret rituals allow the spirit of an ancient knight's mount to animate the cooling corpse of a sacrificial horse. Loyal and obedient, its appearance nevertheless strikes fear into its foes.

T5_MOUNT_COUGAR_KEEPER@1.Description: Keeper scouts have used these fast animals to scout the wilds and will never surrender a cub willingly.

T8_MOUNT_COUGAR_KEEPER@1.Description: The fastest and most aggressive Swiftclaw cubs are raised as Rageclaws: battle mounts for berserker cavalry. Raised from birth to tolerate the fury of battle, Rageclaws deliver their riders right into the heart of the enemy ranks.

T8_MOUNT_ARMORED_HORSE_MORGANA@1.Description: Every Morgana horse-breeder dreams of birthing a foal angry and aggressive enough to survive demonic possession. The resulting creature is almost as dangerous to its rider as it is to its enemies.

T8_MOUNT_RABBIT_EASTER.Description: Spring Cottontails are only found during the Rites of Spring. They're very fast companions, but can grow extremely irritable without a strict diet of chocolate.

T8_MOUNT_RABBIT_EASTER_DARK@1.Description: The Dreaded Rabbit of Caerbann...Caerba...Caerleon. You were warned to only feed it chocolate, but did you listen? Oh, it's just a harmless little bunny, isn't it?

UNIQUE_MOUNT_RAM_XMAS.Description: Mount - With this mount you can celebrate the Midwinter Festival

T7_MOUNT_SWAMPDRAGON_AVALON_BASILISK.Description: A Swamp Dragon infused with Avalonian Energy. Can discharge energy to escape from attackers.

UNIQUE_MOUNT_BAT_TELLAFRIEND.Description: Referral Mount - Can fly on its own, though with a human on top it becomes too heavy to fly over obstacles.

UNIQUE_MOUNT_GIANTTOAD_02_TELLAFRIEND.Description: Mount - Her name is Berta. Born in a backwater swamp, she dreams of someday seeing the world.

T5_MOUNT_ARMORED_HORSE_SKIN_01.Description: An armored horse bearing the impressive banner of its rider's guild. Ideal for raising morale in big battles.

T6_MOUNT_ARMORED_HORSE_SKIN_01.Description: An armored horse bearing the impressive banner of its rider's guild. Ideal for raising morale in big battles.

T7_MOUNT_ARMORED_HORSE_SKIN_01.Description: An armored horse bearing the impressive banner of its rider's guild. Ideal for raising morale in big battles.

T8_MOUNT_ARMORED_HORSE_SKIN_01.Description: An armored horse bearing the impressive banner of its rider's guild. Ideal for raising morale in big battles.

UNIQUE_MOUNT_BAT_PERSONAL.Description: Adventurer's Challenge Reward - Fast and ethereal, with formidable speed and the ability to teleport over short distances.

T7_MOUNT_MONITORLIZARD_ADC.Description: Adventurer's Challenge Reward - Quick and hard to catch, this baleful creature can emit intoxicating poison when threatened.

T7_MOUNT_HUSKY_ADC.Description: Adventurer's Challenge Reward - A very good sprinter with a positive and loyal attitude towards humans.

T6_MOUNT_FROSTRAM_ADC.Description: Adventurer's Challenge Reward - This mount's skillful leap makes it hard to catch.

T7_MOUNT_TERRORBIRD_ADC.Description: Adventurer's Challenge Reward - These animals like to toy with humans, but once trained become very fast and reliable companions.

UNIQUE_MOUNT_BEAR_KEEPER_ADC.Description: Adventurer's Challenge Reward - A strong animal that can easily carry a lot of weight. Its mighty presence alone strikes fear in any attackers.

UNIQUE_MOUNT_BLACK_PANTHER_ADC.Description: Adventurer's Challenge Reward - A real hunter, very swift with the ability to temporarily sprint at high speed to catch any prey.

UNIQUE_MOUNT_MORGANA_RAVEN_ADC.Description: The disciples of Morgana seem to worship this fascinating animal and will likely consider riding it to be heresy.

UNIQUE_MOUNT_GIANT_HORSE_ADC.Description: A heavy horse, also known as Cold Blood. Fearless and not easily impressed by any unforeseen threats.

UNIQUE_MOUNT_UNDEAD_DIREBOAR_ADC.Description: Adventurer's Challenge Reward - Neither burden nor death can stop this beast, which walks in two worlds at once.

UNIQUE_MOUNT_DIVINE_OWL_ADC.Description: Adventurer's Challenge Reward - A being bestowed with divine wisdom and the gift of clairvoyance.

UNIQUE_MOUNT_HERETIC_MULE_ADC.Description: Adventurer's Challenge Reward - An abomination of war that could only have been contrived by the most perverted of minds.

UNIQUE_MOUNT_RHINO_SEASON_CRYSTAL.Description: Guild Season Reward - Exclusive reward for Crystal Rank guild members in Season 4.

UNIQUE_MOUNT_RHINO_SEASON_GOLD.Description: Guild Season Reward - Exclusive reward for Gold Rank guild members in Season 4.

UNIQUE_MOUNT_RHINO_SEASON_SILVER.Description: Guild Season Reward - Exclusive reward for Silver Rank guild members in Season 4.

UNIQUE_MOUNT_RHINO_SEASON_BRONZE.Description: Guild Season Reward - Exclusive reward for Bronze Rank guild members in Season 4.

UNIQUE_MOUNT_TOWER_CHARIOT_CRYSTAL.Description: Battle Mount. Tower mightily over your enemies!

UNIQUE_MOUNT_TOWER_CHARIOT_GOLD.Description: Battle Mount. Tower mightily over your enemies!

UNIQUE_MOUNT_TOWER_CHARIOT_SILVER.Description: Battle Mount. Tower mightily over your enemies!

UNIQUE_MOUNT_ARMORED_EAGLE_CRYSTAL.Description: Battle Mount - its powerful wings can summon a storm.

UNIQUE_MOUNT_ARMORED_EAGLE_GOLD.Description: Battle Mount - its powerful wings can summon a storm.

UNIQUE_MOUNT_ARMORED_EAGLE_SILVER.Description: Battle Mount - its powerful wings can summon a storm.
